Vheadline
p2
VBrilliant shades of Bhairavi
p3
sVnews
p4
VK. Gayathri  gave a pleasing vocal concert during the &#8216;Eppadi Paadinaro&#8217; series  organised by the Rasika Ranjana Sabha, Tiruchi, in association with Sri Krishna Sweets.Gayathri started her recital with  &#8216;Viriboni&#8217; a varnam, in  raga Kedharagowla, Misra Jampai talam, followed by &#8216;Sri Mahaganapathi&#8217; in Gowla. She then thrilled the audience with an impressive alapana in Dharmavathy for  &#8216;Bajanaseyaradha&#8217; with excellent niraval and swara passages.&#8216;Janani&#8217; in Ritigowla was superb. Gayathri took Madhyamavathi as the main raga and her elaborate rendering of the alapana was brilliant and the kriti, &#8216;Paalinchu Kamakshi&#8217; was elegantly rendered. She followed it up with the virutham in seven shades of  raga Bhairavi  and  a  pleasing Meera Bhajan.Gayathri  depicted her excellent concentration and skill in her concluding Thiruppughazh in &#8216;Dwithala Avadhana,&#8217; which is a fete of handling two different talas, Kandajathi Triputa tala Chatursra gathi  and Tisra Jathi Jampa tala Tisra gathi,  simultaneously.T. H. Vasantha ( artist of All India Radio, Tiruchi), on the violin and Koviladi Madhwaprasad on the mridangam, ably supported her throughout.
